      <tr><td colspan=1  style='font-size: 9.5px;'>22 threads, <a href=journal.html?user=49677&start=0>1</a>  page(s) long</td><td  style='font-size: 9.5px;' align=right>&nbsp;</td></tr></table></form><ul><table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101465994258704></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101465994258704><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=49677&mid=101465994258704>"A round of Nerf bats for me and my friends..."</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=49677&mid=101465994258704#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=49677><span id=Guru>alaaraaf the Puissant</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>166 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Mon, Feb 25th 1:00 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.63]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2><i><span style='color: purple;'>&quot;Death is coming;&quot;<br>&quot;I hear it's footsteps...&quot;<br>&quot;Pain is coming;&quot;<br>&quot;I feel it's claws...&quot;<br>&quot;The Dark is coming;&quot;<br>&quot;Nowhere to run now...&quot;<br>&quot;Death is coming;&quot;<br>&quot;It is here!&quot;</span style='color: purple;'><i><br><br>Hey.<br><br>It's patch day.&nbsp;&nbsp;Guess what?  Yep, it snuck up on me again.  <i>(Patch day always sucks, in the Uk.  It's a little after noon and I have another seven hours to go!)</i>  I'm pretty sure my university are emailing Verant with my timetable, to ensure that they patch whenever I'm not at school.  It's the only explanation for it all!  *Grin*<br><br>Speaking of university, I should get my semester one results today.  *Panic*  They should be emailed to me before 14:00.  <i>(One hour and forty minutes.  It's worse than waiting for a patch to end.)</i>  I wasn't tense and stressed before, but I'm heading there.  *Bleaugh*<br><br>Anyhow...<br><br>EverQuest related gibberish...<br><br><LI><b><u>&quot;Behold!  The nerf bat approacheth.&quot;:</u></b><br>It looks very much like the AA ability Dire Charm is in line for a serious whacking with the nerf bat!  For those of you, not in the know, Dire Charm allows you to charm an NPC of up to level forty-six permanently.  Cool, huh?<br><i>(Enchanters can charm anything, Druids can charm animals and Necromancers can charm undead.)</i><br>This has lead to a cycle of bitching in various forums.  The short version of it, being this:<br><i><LI>A mage parses a battle in Kael where a Dire Charmed giant dishes out a little under 30KHPs of damage in a touch under five minutes and posts on a forum.<br><LI>Someone complains that the mage pet was vastly outdamaged by the Dire Charmed giant.<br><LI>Someone announces that Dire Charm is a nerf just waiting to happen.  <br><LI><b>Everyone</b> starts screaming and yelling at one another.  Rioting and looting breaks out...  <i>(Ok, not everyone.  But from the few forums I have read, very few people have been, erm, shall we say serene and at one with their Chi?)</i><br>Personally, I'm not getting involved.  The way things are looking over this, I could post an answer that made everyone happy and I'd get my head ripped off.  <i>(I really do have the answer, honestly!  *Grin*  Oki, there is no answer.  But that doesn't change the screaming and rioting, does it now?)</i><br>Curiously, I fail to see the problem.  *Shrug*  A comment posted to a necromancer forum, regarding this, was something like, &quot;You'd bitch, if mages were given a 5000 point DoT.&quot;  Yeah, someone would bitch.  It doesn't matter what you do, <b>someone</b> is gonna start bitching.  But all the same, I'm not convinced it'd break my heart.  <i>(You have to remember, we're talking about an ability you have to be level fifty nine for <b>and</b> spend (I think) twenty nine AA points to get.  (The only AA ability I have any reservations about, is the wizzie ManaBurn thing.  And then only for PvP, or duelling.  (Which doesn't actually effect me anyhow.)  It should make the next round of BotB events pretty quick!  *Grin*))</i><br>At the end of it, the main statements I've picked up, after what must amount to a coupla hundred posts are:<br><i><LI>Mages have been robbed!  (I don't see it.  Nothing has changed for mages at all!)<br><LI>Dire Charm is over powered!  (Maybe.  But then, it costs a whole lot to get to play with it.)<br><LI>All this whining is gonna get Dire Charm nerfed!  (Definitely.  Maybe this is where I'm missing the point.  Perhaps this is desirable.  *Shrug*  It wouldn't make me happy to see someone else whupped with the nerf bat.  But maybe I'm too ambivalent about this.  Personally, I'm all up for givin' 'em a 5KHP DoT, if it'll make 'em feel better.)<i><br><span style='color: blue;'>It's possibly worth considering at this point, that I don't play an enchanter.  Nor am I likely too, any time soon.  (I played one for a coupla levels and loathed it!)  You might find me as a Shaman, a Wizard, or a Mage, but certainly not an Enchanter.  This being the case, any argument that I'm defending Dire Charm because it benefits me, isn't really any better than that it benefits a mage.  Sure, the Enchanter is dishing out a shedload of damage, through his Dire Charmed pet.  He out damaged you, he out damaged me and hey, we all got a little bit of EXP out of it!  *Shrug*</span style='color: blue;'><br>Ugh!  That took up too much space.  *Grin*<br><br><LI><b><u>Clicky boots:</u></b><br>I finally, after much time and pain, got a pair of Journeyman's boots recently.  All-in-all, I figure I spent about forty hours camping for the AC in OoT.  When I finally got them, I felt rather let down, if the truth be told.  *Sigh*  <br>That sounds a bit odd.  And, no doubt the first thought that runs through your mind as you read it will be, &quot;Well, why the Hell did you camp it, if you don't like it?&quot;  <i>(This of course assumes that it's not something like, &quot;I wonder what's in the kitchen?&quot;, &quot;Just one more page and then I'll log off,&quot; or, &quot;Hey, my porn has finally loaded!&quot;)</i>  Truth is, if I'd known to start with, that it was gonna take so long, I probably wouldn't have.<br>...Or, if I'd known that the effect is substantially slower than SoW and has a far shorter duration.  But I didn't...  <br>They're still a nice item.  And of course, an instant clicky buff, is always a good thing for raids.  <i>(I also attained level fifty-one, so it's about time I started some raiding, no?)</i>  I was just a  little dissapointed.  <span style='color: red;'><b>&quot;Life's hard!  Get a crash helmet!&quot;</b></span style='color: red;'><br><br><i><span style='color: purple;'>&quot;Death is coming;&quot;<br>&quot;It's getting close...&quot;<br>&quot;Pain is coming;&quot;<br>&quot;It's the thing I fear most...&quot;<br>&quot;The Dark is coming;&quot;<br>&quot;My time's almost run...&quot;<br>&quot;Death is coming;&quot;<br>&quot;It is mine!&quot;</span style='color: purple;'><i><br><br><LI><b><u>Is Verant patching my life?</u></b><br>I got my results.  <i>(I'm writing a little and wandering off.  Just writing bits and pieces.  A coupla hours have passed, since I started.)</i>  Actually, I got <b>most</b> of my results.  Out of five modules, my results are:  Two excellent grades.  <i>(Expected.)</i>  One average grade.  <i>(Expected.)</i>  One good'ish grade.  <i>(Dissapointed with this one.)</i> And...  *Drumroll*  One that's missing.  *Sigh*<br>Curiously, this isn't the first time this has happened to me.  This is in fact the third time, one school, or another has just sorta lost my grades.  <i>(That's a bad average, right?  Surely this isn't normal???)</i><br>No big deal.  I called the university.  Erm, well, I tried to.  Today, apparently, my cable company decided was the optimum time to accidentally switch off my 'phoneline.  (I can't even go to the university myself and scream at someone, 'cos my housekeys have vanished.  I have my girlfriend's, but this means she has no keys.  (And I have no means of telling her I have to go out!)  I emailed the plebian who teaches the class, but he's out and won't be in until Friday!)<br>This <b>has</b> to be a conspiricy!  My life has been stealth-nerfed!  *Grin*  Well, perhaps not.  But I'm feelin' pretty lousy about it!  <i>(It doesn't help that the good'ish grade means that barring a minor miracle, I'm gonna have a Hell of a time getting a First class degree, which is what I was aiming for.  *Sigh*)</i><br>Anyhow.  Enough of this.  (Gonna go start cooking and then I'll come back with something about EverQuest.  I guess my life makes pretty dull reading.)<br><br><LI><b><u>&quot;Everquest made my son worship Satan&quot;:</u></b><br>I'm so smart!  I thought of a way to bind my miserable life and EverQuest into a single topic!<br>One of the funniest things I have <b>ever</b> seen on TV was an episode of Sally.  (I'm sure it used to be Sally Jesse Raphael.  Maybe it still is.  I dunno.)  The episode to which I refer, was about parants raiding their kid's rooms, to check up on them.  <i>(In the UK, this is called, &quot;Tidying all your crap, because every time I ask you to do it, you ignore me!&quot;)</i><br>Toward the end of the show, they had a woman on, whose son had apparently gone nuts and killed someone.  After this happened, his mother had cleaned out his room.  She found...  Wait for it...  Pornography and books about guns...  So, she was on TV, sobbing about how if she had checked his room out, she would've known he was gonna turn out bad, because of this!<br><i>(Don't get me wrong, at this point.  I don't doubt that it was genuinely painful to her, that this happened.  And, she probably did believe that porno and guns are a sign of a soon-to-be-murderer.  (Although, she obviously wasn't oo broken up, to milk it, to get her five mins of air time!))</i><br>I'm ninety-nine percent sure, that practically everyone who has kids in the fifteen to twenty age bracket, could find these things in their room.  <span style='color: orange;'>(And if you didn't find it...  Well, you just didn't find it...  Don't kid yourself, it just means they Hide better than you Seek!  *Grin*)</span style='color: orange;'><br>Anyhow, this is one of these things the media seem to keep stored for slow news days.  &quot;Heavy Metal music, turned my kid bad!&quot; - &quot;D&amp;D made my kid a Satanist!&quot; - &quot;Pornography and gun magazines made my kid a murderer!&quot;  I haven't run into, &quot;EverQuest made my kid a serial killing Satanist yet&quot;, but no doubt it's out there...<br>There is a line of reasoning that suggests that fantasy is a good thing.  That it lets you work out things in your life, that you can't deal with, in the conscious mind.  <i>(A chunk of Freudian psychology is based on this idea.)</i>  I'm not entirely sure <b>what</b> it is that I'm working out when I cast a pile of poison spells and drain some poor unfortunate of their life, but I'll work with it...<br>The alternative view is that fantasy is unhealthy.  That it's a way of hiding from real life and not dealing with problems.  At the core of this idea is the suggestion that the desire to be someone, or something else is unhealthy, because you're unsatisfied with your own life.  But...<br>Personally, given the choice, I'm pretty sure I'd rather be a necromancer, armed with knowledge of Death.  (How to bring it...  How to guard against it...  And how to make it your servant...)  <br>Ah well.  Maybe I'm just an unhealthy person.  *Shrug*<br><br><span style='color: green;'>I got a reply from the barrage of eMails I sent to the university about my missing results.  The university, to whom I am paying about £10/hour (~$15/hr) that a lecturer, or other body is present, replied with this:<br><i>The results for SE336 - Visual Basic will not be <br>available til next week. <br>This is due to a problem connecting with the marking process. <br>Please tell anyone else who did this module that <br>there will be this delay.</i><br>Bearing in mind that the deadline for submission was six weeks ago, I'm now curious as to what the Bloody Hell I'm paying for?!?  (And this is ignorin' the minor detail that in this six week period, they declined to tell anyone that a month and a half wasn't enough time to mark it!!!  (Obviously this is because it's my job to tell people????))<br>Oki, I'll leave this alone now.  I'm gonna go and throw up in frustration and put it aside!</span style='color: green;'><br><br><LI><b><u>Clicky boots (revisited):</u></b><br>I had forgotten, in my frustration, why I had originally brought up the issue of clicky boots.  I have been looking through the Allakhazam database for things with clicky effects.  <i>(And I'm currently trying to figure out how best to drag my guild into Kaesora, so I can get a <a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/item.html?item=485 target=_new>Staff of the Dreaded Gaze</a>.)</i>  Oki, stat-wise, it's pretty weak.  Maybe if it was 1HB, it'd work.  BUt for the clicky effect, I just want it.  *Grin*<br>What I have noticed, is that there a good many sets of Kunark armours, with nice clicky effects.  <i>(Elder Spiritist, Jaundiced bone, Blood Ember, etc...)</i>  Iksar seem pretty shafted on these, since they all seem to be plate-class armour, but this shouldn't e an issue for a necromancer.  Except...<br>I can't find one for a necromancer!  <i>(I haven't noticed any for any of the other pure caster classes either!  But at the same time, I haven't looked for one.  It could be there.  But I'm pretty sure there isn't one for a necromancer.)</i>  What I did find for a necromancer, was the XXXX of Condemnation items.  But there're only two of these.  Added to which, they're NO DROP and come from Velketor!  Bah!<br>Where're my clicky toys?  *Pout*<br><br><i><span style='color: purple;'>&quot;Death is coming;&quot;<br>&quot;My shadow draws near...&quot;<br>&quot;Pain is coming;&quot;<br>&quot;I bring you my gift...&quot;<br>&quot;The Dark is coming;&quot;<br>&quot;I walk beneath it's wings...&quot;<br>&quot;Death is coming;&quot;<br>&quot;I bring you release!&quot;</span style='color: purple;'><i><br><br>Well, I don't have anything else to say, just now.  <i>(And I guess I've taken up enough of your time.)</i>  Only an hour of patching to go.  (Only six hours have passed since I started this!  Sheesh!)  Time to tidy a bit.  Maybe my keys'll even turn up!<br><br>I'll probably come back to this post sometime later and tidy it a bit.  I have a feeling it's probably kinda sprawling and odd to read.<br><br>See ya in Norrath.<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
