	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey.<br><br>I am currently working on faction.&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>(As an Iksar necromancer, can this possibly be ethical?  Who knows?  I want a coupla items outta Erudin and if this is what it takes, I guess, this is what I gotta do.  *Growl*)</i><br><br>I started by hunting in the Warrens.  Paineel is delightfully simple, where factions are concerned.  From my wanderings, there seems to be only one faction.  Heretics.  I have come across only one NC who doesn't seem to be on this faction.  <i>(Can't think of his name ofhand.  He's currently dubious.  *Shrug*)</i>  Additionally, raising the Heretic faction is real easy.<br><br><LI><span style='color: purple;'><b>Faction changes from hunting in the Warrens:</b><br>Kobalds killed = 808<br>Factions increased = Heretics &amp; High Guard of Erudin.<br>(Kobald faction <i>(Clan Kolbok)</i> bottomed out after 559 kills.)<br>Current Heretic faction = Amiable.<br>Current High guard faction = dubious.<br>(All other Erudite factions are still KoS.)</span style='color: purple;'><br><br>The skeletal guard in the Paineel newbie garden will not hand over a key to Paineel, until you reach aimiable.  (I tried at both dubious and indifferent and he was having none of it!  *Grin*)  No matter, I'm in now...  Fools!  *Cackle*<br><br>Each guild and the citizens of Erudin each seem to have their own faction.  There are any number of quests to improve these, but the small issue here, is that they all lower Heretic faction.  However, since it is so easy to fix the Heretic faction, my current plan is to work up the Erudin factions and return to the Warrens.  Better yet, on quest involves handing in kobald teeth.  So I'm fixing the Heretic faction, as I collect teeth.<br><br><i>I <b>will</b> walk in the light and bring the dark...  It is just a matter of time...</i><br><br>Anyhow, quite aside from this, since I hauled out my log parser, I thought I'd share a few numbers from the logs.  I have complete logs from October seventh onwards, at which time I was level forty.  (Yes, I have managed the grand total of nine levels in four months!  Hey, I was busy!!!)<br><br><LI><span style='color: purple;'><b>Combat stuff:</b><br>Melee damage taken = 72600</span style='color: purple;'>  (Ouchies!  I have less than a thousand HPs fully buffed!  And this doesn't include damage from HP to mana spells, either!)<span style='color: purple;'><br>Hits taken = 1588</span style='color: purple;'>  (This gives an average damage of forty five.  The maximum single hit being 495!  I can't for the life of me think who hit me for that.)<br><span style='color: purple;'>Magic damage taken = 17423</span style='color: purple;'>  (This doesn't include DoT damage.  I need more HPs.  Lots more Hps!!!<br><br><span style='color: purple;'><b>Casting stuff:</b><br>Casting attempts = 13894<br>Number of fizzles = 506<br>Most commonly casted spell = Invoke Fear</span style='color: purple;'>  (Cast 2249 times!  Hey, I'm a necromancer, this comes as a suprise?  (Dooming Darkness is a close second, at 2159 castings.))<br><br><span style='color: purple;'><b>Miscellaneous stuff:</b><br>Number of deaths = 12</span style='color: purple;'>  (Well, that's not bad!  Twelves deaths in four months...  )<span style='color: purple;'><br>Bloodgill goblins slain, to progress from halfway through level forty-five to level forty-nine = 499.</span style='color: purple;'>  (I think this adequately explains why I'm so sick of them!)<span style='color: purple;'><br></span style='color: purple;'><br><br>Anyhow, that's as much number crunching as I can handle right now.  Gonna go back to hunting faction advances...<br><br>See ya in Norrath.<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
