	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey.<br><br>I have a confession to make.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'm seriously considering making myself a ranger.  Heh.  Two things have led me toward this sorry pass.<br><LI>I went to see the Lord of the Rings a second time last night.  <i>(My girlfriend's daughter also came and was not only bored, but was clearly trying to ensure the entire theatre knew!  If it'd been the first time I went to see it, I think I'd have had to tie her up and sling her behind a row of seats.)</i>  It's definitely the best movie I've seen in ages and ages.  When we came out the first time, my girlfriend asked when part two would be out and she did <b>not</b> look happy, when I told her Christmas.  Heh.<br><LI>After forty-seven levels, I went on my first guild raid, in Kaesora.  (Having been in the guild since about level thirty, but I don't exactly level quickly.)  Among our raiding group, was a ranger in Ivy Etched armour.  I may not like all the new models in SoL, but the Ivy Etched graphics are a work of art.  *Grin*<br>The raid was lotsa fun and made a nice change of pace, from constant solo'ing.  Being an undead zone, I had the chance to put my new Luclin spells into play and spent basically the whole time pretending I was an enchanter and slowing things.  A strange experience.  *Grin*<br>But, between these two inspirations, I think a ranger is a very real possibility.  Once I have the opportunity to acquire some nice items for him, of course.  <i>(I wonder how often Ivy Etched armour goes up for sale in EC...)</i><br><br>Additionally, having sat dormant in level forty-five for so very long, I have now dragged myself halfway through level forty-seven.  (Still well on target for scribing my new spells at level forty-nine on, or before Friday.)<br>Admittedly, I did spend a little time messing around with my shaman.  I have to start paying attention, I got to level seven, before I discovered there were spells at level five!  Doh!  Of course, things picked up a little with the new spells.  (Hit level eight, before lgging.  Only one more level, until I can run about quickly!)<br><br>Anyhow, it's a little after 02:00AM, which means I should be asleep.<br><br>G'night.<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
