	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jan 15th 4:35 PM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey.<br><br>Is it not a wonderful feeling when you survive a horrific near death event?&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>I went hunting in the Crystal Caverns today.  At L45, I'm really a little too high a level to hunt for EXP here.  But, someone recomended that I go hunt Spirocs in the Timorous Deeps.  So, I thought I'd go and load up of crystal silks for Thurgadin gate potions, before I left Velious.<br><br>I started off, grouped with Trackerr, a ranger of around L35.  We were joined by Nexuz, a monk, of around the same level.  So, we decided to see if we could take the queen room.  At this point, everything went a little awry.  <br><br>We pulled the whole queen room!  I dunno exactly what that amounts to.  Personally, I was busy trying to stay alive, rather than counting.  Two Velium crawlers and I'd guess probably five spiders.  (Very fortunately, no drachnids were up!)  The monk spent half the fight FD, since he got his ass kicked real fast.  <i>(What do you expact?  Monks aren't exactly a tank class!)</i>  <br><br>We won with no deaths!  No that it was a clean victory.  Trackerr and Nexuz ended with less than half a bubble of life.  I ended up with almost exactly one bubble.  The pet died and both Trackerr and I were out of mana.  I even tanked the last spider, for most of the fight!  <i>(I want platemail, dammit!)</i>  But we <b>did</b> win.<br><br>It didn't even end there.  Almost immediately, respawned wanderers from the tunnel started to attack us.  (I think maybe two spiders.  Not enough that I'd be in the least concerned, with a pet and half mana.)  An attack that should have been a breeze, but in the circumstances, life-threatening.  Again, we fought to victory, without casualty.<br><br>A brief respite now.  The tunnel clear of foes both ahead and behind.  Vanquished and we stood victorious, yet bloodied and weary to the bone.<br><br>Still, the caverns would not relinquish us as prey!  By the time we had all recovered to about half health and I had restored my pet, another wave struck.  <i>(I think I had about half mana, by this point!)</i>  Another attack of wandering spiders struck.  Not the end of the world, by this point, but still not an ideal situation.  But, during this fight, the Drachnid Retainer choose to leave the Queen room and engage us!<br><br>And again, we arose from the gore and slaughter victorious.  Though once again, we were torn and bloodied.<br><br>And it felt good.  Death had reached forth, but was thwarted.  For a total of maybe twenty, or twenty-five minutes, we'd stood at the threshold of the shadow and we survived.  <br><br>Anyhow, I thought I'd share this little episode with you.  That's all for now.<br><br>I'm bound for the Timorous Deeps...<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
