ink they'll discuss it with me reasonably?  Not a hope in Hell.  They'll beat the @#%^ outta me.  Do you see a similarity?)</i>  I also made the remark that the people who genuinely hate you aren't worth worrying about.<br><i>...End of thread...</i><br><LI><b><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=91720&amp;mid=100673933966083 target=_new>EQ revisited</a></b><br>You logged into EQ, saw nothing had changed and came back to complain about this.  You also took up the issue of PvP and Roleplay.<br>My response was that nothing had changed, because the vast majority of customers are happy'ish and don't feel a pressing need for change.  And, furthermore, that PvP and Roleplay <b>aren't</b> the domain of the majority of paying customers.  And therefore they're a pretty low priority.<br>We then continued with you expressing that Verant exists to provide a service and are failing to do this.  I explained that they don't exist to provide a service.  They exist to make a <b><span style='color: green;'>profit</span style='color: green;'></b>.  And they will do the absolute minimum necessary to acheive this.<br><i>...End of thread...</i><br><LI><b><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=91720&amp;mid=100801811944141 target=_new>Conduct clause</a></b><br>You posted a parody conduct clause, describing Verant's obligations.  Essentially, it boiled down to, 'you pay and we're not required to ensure you're happy.'<br>My reply was to state that practically every company in the world work on this basis.  Verant aren't an unusually cruel, or evil company.  They're just like everyone else.<br>I did agree with what you said, if you read my post.  But at the same time, I thought you were perhaps being naive to expect that it would be any different.<br><i>...End of thread...</i><br><LI><b><a href=HTTP://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/journal.html?user=91720&amp;mid=101060314620095 target=_new><span style='color: red;'>Dave Thomas 1933-2002<