 from now on I will stay away from doing rants like the last one, NOT!!! If I actually stopped doing rants from the amount of hatred I got, I would have quit a long ago.</i><br>Aside from the first sentence being a horrible abuse of the English language, your statement is built upon a faulty premise.  You didn't get any hatred.  You got an honest opinion, who thought that you said something that was not entirely true.  Nor did you get flamed, you got a perfectly rational explanation of why I felt your remarks were misplaced.<br><br>So, that covers my posts in your journal.  There were actually fewer than I thought.  Having said which, some are pretty huge, so maybe that accounts for it.  It is true, that I never posted a congratulary, 'Roshi you're wonderful' remark.  Is that what you really wanted?  What I gave you was something far more unusual.  I gave you the truth, from my point of view.  In every instance, I gave you a fair and rational reply <b>and</b> I took the time to justify why I had said what I said.<br><br>To me, that is far more valuable, than posting how great you are.  I could have just given you a lousy rating.  I think you'll find that's the normal response to reading something one disagrees with.  <i>(Both here and on any other message board, or forum.)</i>  Or, I could have flamed you, telling you how worthless your remarks are, without applying any constructive structure to my remarks.<br><br>I take care that I don't post, unless I have something I feel is useful to say.  I don't wander the boards flaming people.  Nor do I offend people, if it is avoidable.  I am a purveyor of (what I see as) the Truth.  Further, I take care to justify why I believe what I say is the Truth.<br><br>I think you'll probably find that the reason you feel my remarks are '<i>allot more sane</i>' here, is because you're not taking personal affront to what I say.  Either way, I will no longer be posting in your journal, so you forget I was ever there and no longer concern yourself that I always have a bone to pick with you.<br><br>However, we can go one further...<br><br><span style='color: purple;'><b>If anyone has the time to read through Roshi's journal, or has read through it previously and has a good recollection, I would appreciate your opinion:</b><br><LI>Have I been unfairly picking on Roshi?<br><LI>Did I at some point go insane and start posting abject bollocks?<br><LI>Is there a significant difference in style, or content between what I have posted on Roshi's journal and what I post anywhere else?<br>I would appreciate some feedback on this one.  <i>(The written type, don't come to my flat and start screwing about with the wiring!)</i></span style='color: purple;'><br><br>Now, I have an exam to sit, in sixty one minutes, so it is time I make myself scarce!  :)<br><br>AlAaraaf.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
