<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=101186724423606></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f101186724423606><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=49677&mid=101186724423606>RE: Customer service and petitions....</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=49677&mid=101186724423606#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=46554><span id= >grishnak</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>24 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jan 24th 6:15 AM 2002</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.40]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>A note on Petition #4. I couldn't agree more with your assesment of the GM's lack of a response. It is poor CS and no amount of excuse making will render it otherwise. That having been said, this is not a bug. When a character zones they still exist in the zone they left for a brief period od time. This is not unlike what happens when you go Link Dead though for a much shorter period of time. This phenomenon is best observed while following another player as you hit the zone line. The character ahead of you will seem to continue to run past the zone line. In fact when following a character in this manner I have rarely seen the character ahead of me disappear before I myself get the LOADING PLEASE WAIT message unless I am quite far behind even though they had obviously reached the zone line before me. So what happend in your case was you clicked the orb and got the LOADING message but your body was still in the zone for a a second or two, long enough for you to be slain by the mobs in pursuit. One might argue whether this should be the case but it is not a bug in the sense that it is working just as intended, just like when you sit down in a house in East Karana only to be attacked by a passing Lion.. or worse. Having said all of the above, this is still no excuse for the GM to not have responded to your Email.<br><br>Awesome Journal by the way though I have read only a small part.<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
