	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hey.<br><br><i>That having been said, this is not a bug. When a character zones they still exist in the zone they left for a brief period od time.</i><br>I didn't know this.&nbsp;&nbsp;I do now.  I'm not happy that it works like this, but it's a good thing to know.  Basically, it translates into:<br><br><i><span style='color: purple;'><b>&quot;Run earlier...&quot;</b></span style='color: purple;'></i><br><br>The only silly thing, is that the GM <b>must</b> know about this.  And, working on the assumption that he knows, he coulda saved himself (and the guide) a whole lot of time by simply telling me that.<br><br>Personally, I have reached the stage where I don't even bother to petition.  It's just not worth the effort of typing the words.  *Sigh*  I'd like to believe that this will improve, with competition, but honestly, I doubt it will.  (Look at the way other businesses work.  In theory, competition should improve service and lower cost.  In practise, businesses seem to have decided on a cost between them and agreed they'll all treat their customer's like something you scrape off your shoes.)<br><br>Still, I enjoy EverQuest greatly.  So, I'll just ignore the guides, who're too powerless to be useful and the GM's, who're too busy, erm, frankly, I don't know what the Hell they're doin'.  Masterbating in their offices, or something probably.  *Shrug*<br><br>I'm glad you're enjoying the journal.  (It's sorta gone off the tracks somewhere.  It's not in character.  It's not really out of character.  It's just, well, it's meandering...  Just as the title suggests.  No-one seems too unhappy about it, so I'll just continue blindly crashing through the bushes.)<br><br>AlAaraaf...............................<i>A little wiser now.</i><br><br>&nbsp;<br>"Te aurdire no possum. Musa sapienum fixa est in aura."</td></tr>
